ed by Victor Cousin, this long-lived project singled out the male bourgeoisie for training in selfhood --Cousin and his disciples deemed workers and women incapable of the introspective finesse necessary to appropriate that self in practice.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 08. Jul 2019) 0aEgo (Psychology) 0aMiddle classzFrancexHistoryy18th century. 0aMiddle classzFrancexHistoryy19th century. 0aMonomania. 0aPsychiatryzFrancexHistoryy18th century. 0aPsychiatryzFrancexHistoryy19th century. 0aSelfxSocial aspectszFrancexHistoryy18th century. 0aSelfxSocial aspectszFrancexHistoryy19th century. 7aHISTORY / Europe / France.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311044220508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z978311045951708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2015z978311066256640uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/9780674037786423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780674037786.jpg  a978-3-11-044220-5  HUP eBook Package Backlist 2005-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-045951-7  HUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014c2000d2014  a978-3-11-066256-6  HUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG  aPDA8HUP